subsection.p:
The efficiency for the Otto cycle, derived below, is similar to that of Carnot cycle, except the fact that here we do not have a constant temperature bath.

	\eta_{\text{Otto;Ideal}} = 1- \frac{T_4}{T_3} = 1- \frac{T_1}{T_2} 

where T_1 is the temperature of the chamber at the beginning of the adiabatic compression stroke and T_2 the temperature at the end of the compression.
